definition.value: A 2'-deoxynucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2'-deoxy-purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-phosphate; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A monocarboxylic acid anion and organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of both the carboxy group and the phosphate group of ditrans,polycis-dodecaprenyl phosphate-GalA. The major species at pH 7.3.
A monoglyceride in which the acyl group contains a total of 18 carbon atoms and 4 double bonds.
A lysophosphatidylethanolamine in which the acyl group has a fully saturated C15 chain and is attached to the glycero moiety at either position 1 or 2.
A retinoid that is all-trans-3,4-didehydroretinol in which the double bond alpha- to the the terminal hydroxy group has been reduced to a single bond.
A 2-(3,4-dihydroxyphenyl)-2,5,7-trihydroxy-2,3-dihydro-4H-chromen-4-one that has (R) configuration.
A pentahydroxyflavanone carrying the hydroxy groups at positions 2,3', 4', 5 and 7.
A 2,5,7-trihydroxy-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)-2,3-dihydro-4H-chromen-4-one that has (R) configuration.
A tetrahydroxyflavanone carrying the hydroxy groups at positions 2, 4', 5 and 7.
A 2,5,7-trihydroxy-2-phenyl-2,3-dihydro-4H-chromen-4-one that has (R) configuration.
A trihydroxyflavanone carrying the hydroxy groups at positions 2,5 and 7.
Meromycolic acids are one of the two precursor of the mycolic acids produced by Mycobacteria. They consist of a long chain typically of 50-60 carbons, which is functionalized by different groups.
A dipeptide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of threonine with the amino group of cysteic acid.
An arene epoxide that is tetraphene which has undergone 1,2 addition of an oxygen atom to the double bond at the 5-6 position.
A hexadecenoic acid having a trans-double bond at the 3-position.
An organic heterohexacyclic compound that is 3-methylcholanthrene which has undergone epoxidation by the formal 1,2-addition of an oxygen atom to the double bond at the 11-12 position.
A primary fatty amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of erucic acid with ammonia. It is commonly used as a slip additive in the plastic manufacturing industry.
An omega-hydroxy-long-chain fatty acid that is hexadecanoic acid substituted by an oxo group at position 10 and by a hydroxy group at position 16.
An octadecadiynoic acid having its triple bonds at positions 9 and 12.
A carbocyclic compound that is 3,5-di-sec-butylcyclopentene which is substituted by a 4-carboxy-1,3,4-trihydroxybutyl group at position 1.
